claim.claim-text:
1. A system for chemical deposition at ambient temperature using electron cyclotron resonance (ECR) comprising: 
a process chamber; 
a substrate, on which a specimen is mounted, installed in the process chamber; 
an ECR system connected to the process chamber for providing plasma; 
a supply system for providing the process chamber with organic material or organo-metallic compound; 
a sputtering system for providing the process chamber with metal ion; 
an induced voltage supply system for inducing the metal ion and radical ion on the specimen which is mounted on the substrate; 
a grid installed around the substrate for inducing the metal ion and the radical ion to the specimen by being applied the voltage provided from the induced voltage supply system; and 
a vacuum system connected to the process chamber for controlling an inner vacuumed degree.

2. The system of claim 1, wherein the ECR system comprises: 
a generator for generating microwave; 
a gas supply unit providing gas for forming plasma; 
an ECR chamber in which the plasma by the ECR is formed; 
at least one magnet mounted on the ECR chamber for forming a magnetic field; 
a waveguide for providing the ECR chamber with the microwave; and 
an impedance matching unit connected to the waveguide between the ECR chamber and the generator for impedance matching.

7. A method for fabricating metal composite film using ECR comprising: 
a step of providing gas as plasma form into a chamber in which reaction is made using ECR characteristic; 
a step of providing the chamber with metal ion and organic material; 
a step of generating for generating organic material ion and radical ion by reacting the metal ion and the organic material with the plasma; and 
a step of inducing the organic material ion and the radical ion on a surface of a specimen and chemically compounding them.
